This paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category as it deals with the popularity of software packages and their reuse in software systems. It could also belong to Programming Languages (cs.PL) as it discusses the use of open source libraries and package managers. Additionally, it could be classified under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as it analyzes popularity metrics and their relationship. Cybersecurity and Cryptography (cs.CY) could also be a possible category as the paper deals with tracking systems and data sampling. Finally, Computer Science and Game Theory (cs.GT) could be another possible category as the paper discusses the concept of popularity and its measurement, which could be relevant to game theory.
